This paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on how a reinforcement learning agent can use previous experience to improve its ability to solve new problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are directly related to reinforcement learning. The other categories are also relevant as they deal with related topics such as control and optimization.
